node.text: Tesla speed 😂⚡️ Can yall guess how many punches I threw ? 👀 #boxing #speed

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Marc Castro in Fresno, California. May be an image of 1 person, biceps, standing and indoor.

node.text: My life has dramatically changed these last 2 months. I’m talking about the stuff you don’t see on social media. My mindset, my perspective & my actions on life & boxing. After losing my grandma, I was down & just empty inside with no motivation. With the help of God & my loved ones, I slowly got out of that dark place. I just started grinding like crazy & kept reminding myself why I’m doing this. I took this pic & realize I’m proud of myself & with the progress I made in these last weeks. I’m not where I want to be yet, but I’m definitely becoming better daily. I feel in the best shape of my life!! It’s a thing of beauty when your mind, soul & heart are on the same page. I can’t wait to showcase my skills my next fight which I’ll be announcing soon! Much love to all my supporters 🤞🏻❤️ #TeamCastro #loveyall

node.text: Grandma I’m sitting in your house wondering when you will come home again?? But I realized you’re already home..in heaven where you always belonged. This doesn’t feel real, you’re the strongest person I know. I never experienced losing someone this close to me, my grandma means so much to me. Nana we miss you so much, I don’t even know where to start. Everyone tells me how proud you were of me, but I know deep down if I never achieve anything you would be proud regardless. Thank you for raising us & giving us the best advice. But there’s one thing I hate, you taught us everything..everything except how to live without you 💔💔 we love you forever & always our queen! 🤞🏻❤️ #iloveyou #grandma
